# Agentic Loop PR Code Review (`your-service-*`)

On-demand workflow for reviewing pull requests. Complements [service-quality-drill.mdc](./service-quality-drill.mdc) (build/JaCoCo/CI/fix) ‚Äî this rule owns **context ‚Üí review ‚Üí humanized comment tables**.

Also apply [java-springboot-standards.mdc](./java-springboot-standards.mdc) for all Java/Spring Boot patterns.

**Invoke:** `@pr-code-review` + PR URL/number, or "review this PR using our code review rule".

**Default mode:** report-only ‚Äî do not auto-apply fixes or commit unless the user explicitly asks.

## Workflow overview

```
Phase 0 (PR + Jira + type + feedback registry) ‚Üí Pass 1 ‚Üí Pass 2 ‚Üí Pass 3 (routed by pr_type) ‚Üí synthesize ‚Üí net-new table
```

---

## Phase 0 ‚Äî Functional context (mandatory first)

**Do not start ce-code-review or Bugbot until Phase 0 is complete.**

### 0a. PR metadata and discussion

```bash
gh pr view <n-or-url> --json title,body,baseRefName,headRefName,url,comments,reviews
gh pr view <n-or-url> --comments   # when thread detail is needed
```

Write a **Functional Context** block (3‚Äì8 bullets):

- **Intent** ‚Äî what the PR claims to deliver.
- **Acceptance signals** ‚Äî must/should language, checklists in description.
- **Review thread themes** ‚Äî unresolved or recently resolved comments defining expected behavior.
- **Out of scope** ‚Äî explicit deferrals.

If no PR exists, use commit messages + linked docs; note `context_source: branch-only`.

### 0b. Jira ticket discovery and fetch

Scan PR title, body, commits, and review comments for keys: `[A-Z][A-Z0-9]+-\d+` (e.g. `PROJ-123`).

For each unique key:

1. Fetch via **Atlassian MCP** `getJiraIssue` (preferred).
2. Fallback: Glean search or compiled [jira-backlog.md](../docs/wiki/jira-backlog.md) if MCP unavailable ‚Äî note `jira_context: partial|unavailable` in header.

Capture: summary, status, type, description/AC, parent epic, edge cases/NFRs.

Append **Jira scope** (key ‚Üí requirement) and **requirements trace** (files/methods ‚Üí AC). If fetch fails, add P2 row for missing context and continue.

### 0c. Scenario matrix (pre-review sketch)

| Scenario type | Verify in code/tests |
|---------------|----------------------|
| **Positive** | Primary flows from PR/Jira |
| **Negative** | Invalid input, auth denied, dependency down, not-found |
| **Edge** | null/blank, empty collections, timeouts, concurrency, idempotency, stale cache |
| **Runtime tier** | For workflow/test PRs: estimate wall time from scripts; flag suites likely **>10 min** as nightly/scheduled candidates, not per-push blockers |

### 0d. Existing PR thread ingestion (mandatory when PR exists)

Fetch inline review comments and map them to the diff before Pass 1:

```bash
gh api "repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{n}/comments?per_page=100" \
  --jq '.[] | {id, user: .user.login, path, line, body, in_reply_to_id}'
```

For each thread:

- Summarize **unresolved** themes and **recently resolved** behavior the author committed to.
- **Elevate manager/staff feedback** to **P1 Requirements** when it conflicts with an added hunk ‚Äî cite the thread id (e.g. `r3423687036`) in **Sources**.
- Map each thread to a **`+` line** in the diff (`git diff -U0 base...head -- <file>`). Skip threads anchored on unchanged context lines unless the thread still applies to nearby added code.
- Include **Review thread themes** in the Functional Context block (0a) with author replies and open disagreements.

Pass Functional Context + scenario checklist + PR thread themes to ce-code-review intent and Bugbot `Custom Instructions`.

### 0e. PR-type classification (mandatory when PR exists)

Classify before Pass 1 from changed file paths:

```bash
gh pr diff <n-or-url> --name-only
# or: git diff --name-only origin/<base>...HEAD
```

| `pr_type` | Diff signals |
|-----------|----------------|
| **java-only** | Only `your-service-*/**`, `*.java`, `build.gradle.kts`, `src/**` under your-service repos |
| **infra-only** | Only `infra//**`, `DDog_1000896_iac_live/**`, `*.tf`, `deployment.y*ml`, `.github/workflows/**` ‚Äî **no** Java paths |
| **mixed** | Both Java and infra path sets |

Record in Functional Context header: `pr_type: java-only | infra-only | mixed`.

**Route Pass 3 and quality drill by `pr_type`:**

| `pr_type` | Pass 3 | Quality drill |
|-----------|--------|---------------|
| java-only | ¬ß3a‚Äì3d (below) + [java-springboot-standards.mdc](./java-springboot-standards.mdc) + ArchUnit | [service-quality-drill.mdc](./service-quality-drill.mdc): gradle, JaCoCo, CI |
| infra-only | ¬ß3e infra (below); **skip** ¬ß3a‚Äì3d ArchUnit | No JaCoCo/gradle; `terraform fmt`/`validate` if `.tf`; **no** `terraform apply` |
| mixed | ¬ß3a‚Äì3d on Java `+` hunks only; ¬ß3e on infra `+` hunks; **Cross-cutting** rows when TF + Java consumer linked | Per-segment gates |

**Mixed PR rules:** Java findings cite `+` lines under `your-service-*`; infra findings cite `+` under `infra/` / DDog / workflows. Do not apply Java layering to `.tf` or workflow YAML.

### 0f. Existing-feedback registry (mandatory when PR exists)

Run after Phase 0d. Build a dedup registry so synthesis does not repeat open threads.

```bash
# Inline review comments (humans + bots on diff lines) ‚Äî may overlap 0d
gh api "repos/{owner}/{repo}/pulls/{n}/comments?per_page=100"

# PR conversation comments
gh api "repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues/{n}/comments?per_page=100"

# Review summaries (APPROVE / REQUEST_CHANGES)
gh pr view <n-or-url> --json reviews
```

**Registry row:** `(path, line ¬±3, author, thread_id, theme_summary, resolved, bot)`

Tag bot authors: `github-copilot[bot]`, `copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]`, `github-codequality[bot]`, `advanced-security[bot]`, `copilot-swe-agent[bot]`.

Include in Functional Context:

```markdown
## Existing feedback registry (Phase 0f)
- Open threads: N | Resolved: M | Bots: B
- Themes already raised: [path:line ‚Äî author ‚Äî theme_summary]
```

Pass registry to ce-code-review Stage 2 and Bugbot: **"Do not re-raise themes in Existing feedback registry unless diff changed since that comment."**

