## Pass 1 ‚Äî ce-code-review

- Run **`ce-code-review`** skill (full multi-agent pipeline ‚Äî not quick-review short-circuit).
- Scope: PR URL/number; else current branch vs `main` (`base:origin/main`).
- Inject Phase 0 intent (PR + Jira + scenarios + PR threads + **0f registry** + **`pr_type`**) into ce-code-review Stage 2.
- **Skip Stage 5c auto-apply** unless user asked to fix.
- Capture: verdict, P0‚ÄìP3, persona, file, line, suggested fix, testing gaps.

### Diff-only scoping (mandatory for PR reviews)

Findings must cite **only added lines** from the PR diff:

```bash
git fetch origin pull/{n}/head:refs/review/pr-{n}-head   # when reviewing a PR
git diff -U0 main...refs/review/pr-{n}-head -- <file>    # verify each Location
```

- **Location** column: file path + line number that appears on a **`+` hunk** in `-U0` diff output.
- Pre-existing code (unchanged lines, pre-existing workflow steps) ‚Üí **requirements trace**, **pre-existing gaps**, or **Review thread themes** ‚Äî not new findings.
- If a colleague comment targets pre-existing code, note it under Functional Context or a separate **Pre-existing gaps** section; do not assign a diff Location unless the PR also adds/changes that line.

